# Dashboard layout spacing

Use Chakra `Stack` / `Flex` with `gap` from shared layout primitives. Do **not** use Tailwind `space-y-*` on dashboard pages.

See `responsive-ui.mdc` for breakpoint behavior on phones and tablets.

## Imports

```ts
import {
  ButtonGroup,
  DetailFieldRow,
  EventPageLayout,
  LAYOUT_GAP,
  PageHeader,
  PageStack,
  PanelCard,
} from '@/components/dashboard'
```

## Spacing scale (`LAYOUT_GAP`)

| Token | Value | Use |
|-------|-------|-----|
| `page` | 6 | Major page blocks |
| `section` | 6 | Between sibling cards |
| `form` | 4 | Form fields / field groups |
| `buttons` | 3 | Adjacent action buttons |
| `cardPadding` | 6 | Inside `PanelCard` (at `lg+`; `base` uses 4) |
| `cardTitle` | 4 | Below card titles |
| `pagePadding` | `{ base: 4, md: 5, lg: 6 }` | Dashboard main content padding |

## Responsive spacing

- `PageStack`, `PanelCard`, and dashboard `main` use responsive padding: `base: 4`, `md: 5`, `lg: 6`.
- `PageHeader` actions must stack on `base` (title block above actions).

## Page wrappers

| Route type | Wrapper |
|------------|---------|
| Event tab pages | `EventPageLayout` (tabs + content with `gap={6}`) |
| All other dashboard pages | `PageStack` |

```tsx
// Event tab page
return (
  <EventPageLayout eventId={event.id} eventName={event.name}>
    <FeatureClient ... />
  </EventPageLayout>
)

// Standard dashboard page
return (
  <PageStack>
    <PageHeader title="..." description="..." actions={...} />
    <PanelCard title="...">...</PanelCard>
  </PageStack>
)
```

## Components

- **`PageHeader`** — page title, optional description, optional actions slot
- **`PanelCard`** — bordered card sections (replaces `Box borderWidth="1px"`)
- **`DetailFieldRow`** — label/value rows that stack on `base`
- **`ButtonGroup`** — two or more adjacent buttons (stacks on `base`)
- **`Stack gap={LAYOUT_GAP.form}`** — inside forms between fields

## Do not

- Raw `Box borderWidth="1px"` for dashboard sections — use `PanelCard`
- `className="space-y-6"` on dashboard pages — use `PageStack`
- Inline `style={{ marginTop: ... }}` for button spacing — use `ButtonGroup` or `mt={LAYOUT_GAP.form}`
- Fragment (`<>`) between `EventDetailTabs` and page content — use `EventPageLayout`
